      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "low",
      "summary": "SyncPage uses loadHistoryRef to break circular useCallback dependency \u2014 correct but adds cognitive overhead",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "logic_clarity",
        "related_files": [
          "frontend/src/pages/SyncPage.jsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "SyncPage.jsx uses pollRef and loadHistoryRef refs to break a loadHistory\u2194startPolling circular useCallback dependency. The 4-step lifecycle (loadHistory -> startPolling -> poll completes -> loadHistoryRef.current()) requires understanding that startPolling calls loadHistory indirectly through a ref kept in sync by a separate useEffect."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Consider useReducer to manage sync page state (displayedJob, history, isRunning) in a single reducer, which would eliminate the circular dependency. The polling logic could dispatch actions rather than calling state setters through refs.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
