    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_error_strategies_across_components::abffd64c": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::mixed_error_strategies_across_components::abffd64c",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Components use three different error strategies (try-catch, return null, throw) without a coherent policy",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "frontend/src/components/AIAnalysisPanel.jsx",
          "frontend/src/components/AccountsBreakdown.jsx",
          "frontend/src/components/BudgetChart.jsx",
          "frontend/src/components/GroupManager.jsx",
          "frontend/src/api.js"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "api.js consistently throws on HTTP errors, which is good. But components handle those errors inconsistently: AIAnalysisPanel, GroupManager, SyncControl use try-catch; AccountsBreakdown, BudgetChart, GroupsSnapshot, StatsCards return null/loading for missing data; BudgetTable returns null silently. There is no documented convention for when to use which strategy, and sibling components at the same layer (e.g. AccountsBreakdown vs AIAnalysisPanel) diverge.",
          "Pages also diverge: GroupsPage shows a full-page error block on fetch failure, BudgetPage shows an inline error box, SyncPage shows a top-level error banner. These are different UX patterns for the same failure mode."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Establish an error display convention per component layer: pages should use a consistent error-state pattern (either full-page or inline), and leaf components should consistently handle null/undefined data the same way (either loading skeleton or return null). Document this in conventions.md. The current mixed approaches are not wrong individually but the inconsistency makes the codebase harder to reason about.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "wontfix",
      "note": "GroupsPage hook extraction and prop passthrough removal are large architectural refactors best done in a focused session. Error strategy standardization requires a product decision on UX patterns. Package reorganization into subdirectories would break all imports and tests simultaneously \u2014 better as a standalone PR.",
