    "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::groupspage_orchestration_complexity::367afe12": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::groupspage_orchestration_complexity::367afe12",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "GroupsPage.jsx manages 8 state variables, 6 callbacks, and passes 11 props through to GroupsSnapshot \u2014 high coordination burden",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "frontend/src/pages/GroupsPage.jsx",
          "frontend/src/components/GroupsSnapshot.jsx",
          "frontend/src/components/GroupSnapshotControls.jsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "GroupsPage (191 LOC, complexity score 322 per blind packet) manages: groups, accounts, historyData, snapshot, configs, activeConfigId, selectedGroupIds, loading, error \u2014 9 useState calls plus 1 useMemo (conflictMap) and 1 useMemo (filteredSnapshot). It defines 5 useCallback handlers (handleGroupToggle, handleSelectConfig, handleSaveConfig, handleDeleteConfig, handleRenameConfig) that are all passed through GroupsSnapshot to GroupSnapshotControls.",
          "GroupsSnapshot receives 11 props and passes 9 of them straight through to GroupSnapshotControls. GroupsSnapshot itself only uses snapshot, groups (for showControls check), and the responsive hook. The remaining 9 props are pure passthrough.",
          "This prop-drilling pattern means any change to the config management API requires touching 3 files in sequence: GroupsPage -> GroupsSnapshot -> GroupSnapshotControls."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract the snapshot config state management (configs, activeConfigId, selectedGroupIds, conflictMap, and the 5 handlers) into a custom hook like useSnapshotConfigs({ groups }). GroupsPage would call the hook and spread the returned object to GroupsSnapshot. This would reduce GroupsPage from 9 state variables to 4 (groups, accounts, historyData, loading/error) and make the config management logic independently testable.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "wontfix",
      "note": "GroupsPage hook extraction and prop passthrough removal are large architectural refactors best done in a focused session. Error strategy standardization requires a product decision on UX patterns. Package reorganization into subdirectories would break all imports and tests simultaneously \u2014 better as a standalone PR.",
