        "dimension": "test_strategy",
        "related_files": [
          "frontend/src/pages/SyncPage.test.jsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Multiple tests use vi.advanceTimersByTime(2100) which assumes the poll interval is 2000ms. If the interval constant in SyncPage.jsx changes (e.g., to 3000ms for rate limiting), these tests will silently pass without actually triggering polls, giving false confidence."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract the poll interval as a named constant from SyncPage and import it in tests, or use vi.advanceTimersToNextTimer() instead of hardcoded millisecond values.",
